HEADWORD: Cotidal
<hw>Co*tid"al</hw> <pr>(k?-t?d"<it>a</it>l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Marking an equality in the tides; having high tide at the same
time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cotidal lines</b></col> <fld>(Phys. Geog.)</fld>,
<cd>lines on a map passing through places that have high tide at the
same time.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

